<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
    ServiceNow Update Set record-definition for the `sys_dictionary` row that
    declares the `subject` String field on the `x_[scope]_case_task` custom
    table inside the scoped application `x_[scope]_case_management`.

    Per AAP Section 0.5.7 (Data-Model Mapping verbatim) for x_[scope]_case_task:

        Field      Type           Constraints
        subject    String(255)    Mandatory

    THIS FIELD IS THE PRIMARY HUMAN-READABLE IDENTIFIER OF EVERY TASK ROW.
    It captures the short summary or title that surfaces in every place a
    user encounters a task:
      - the auto-generated x_[scope]_case_task list view (AAP Section 0.4.4
        "Internal user UI" requires "ServiceNow's automatic native list
        and form views for the three custom tables")
      - the auto-generated form layout when a user opens an individual
        task record
      - the parent case's Related List of tasks (rendered via the `case`
        reference field declared in ../dictionary/x_[scope]_case_task_case.xml;
        the user sees `subject` in the Subject column of that related list)
      - the `My overdue tasks` list report on the Agent Workspace dashboard
        (AAP Section 0.5.1: list report filtered by
        `due_date < javascript:gs.daysAgoStart(0) AND status != Closed AND
        assigned_to = javascript:gs.getUserID()` - subject is the
        at-a-glance identifier of which task is overdue)
      - the synthetic seed data per AAP Section 0.7.4 minimum-data threshold
        (at least one open and one closed task on selected demo cases per
        AAP Section 0.3.1, all with realistic non-PII summary phrases)

    Without this field, every other column on x_[scope]_case_task (case,
    type, status, assigned_to, due_date) describes attributes of a
    nameless task. Subject is the field that gives a task its identity
    in the eyes of a human user.

    Semantic source-side reference (read-only, NOT byte-for-byte ported):
      - acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-task-plugin/src/main/java/
        com/armedia/acm/plugins/task/model/AcmTask.java lines 67-68:
            @Size(min = 1)
            private String title;
        ArkCase's task title was a Bean Validation-constrained String on
        the AcmTask domain object (the source-side analog of this
        ServiceNow table). The `@Size(min = 1)` annotation (imported on
        line 50 from `javax.validation.constraints.Size`) enforces a
        non-empty value at the JSR-380 validator layer - effectively a
        NOT-NULL-AND-NOT-EMPTY check at the entry-point of every
        AcmTask-mutating Spring service. The ServiceNow target replaces
        both the Java field declaration AND the @Size constraint with
        this single dictionary entry: `mandatory=true` is the platform-
        native equivalent of `@Size(min=1)`, and the
        `<max_length>255</max_length>` ceiling caps overlong values
        without a custom validator. The platform enforces mandatory on
        every insert / update through the standard form, the Table API,
        and any seed-script GlideRecord.insert() invocation.
      - The field name is `subject` (lowercase, 7 chars; NOT `title`,
        NOT `task_title`, NOT `taskTitle`) per AAP Section 0.5.7 verbatim.
        This is an INTENTIONAL rename from ArkCase: AAP Section 0.5.1
        explicitly renames `title` -> `subject` so that BOTH
        x_[scope]_case AND x_[scope]_case_task carry identically-named
        human-readable summary columns. The naming symmetry matters at
        multiple layers:
          * Cross-table list views and reports can render a unified
            "Subject" column header without per-table label aliasing.
          * The Agent Workspace dashboard's "My open cases" list (parent
            case subject) and "My overdue tasks" list (task subject)
            both surface a Subject column using the same field
            identifier, simplifying report authoring and dashboard
            template binding.
          * The case form's task Related List uses `subject` as the
            primary display column, and the case form's own subject
            field shares the same label - users see "Subject" twice on
            the case form (once for the case, once per related task)
            without confusing terminology.
      - ArkCase's source `title` field had no explicit length cap in the
        Bean Validation annotations on AcmTask.java (AcmTask is a domain
        object passed through the Activiti BPMN engine, not a directly-
        persisted JPA entity in the same sense as CaseFile.java; the
        underlying ACT_HI_TASKINST.NAME_ column in the Activiti H2/MySQL
        history schema defaults to VARCHAR(255)). AAP Section 0.5.7
        codifies the ServiceNow-side cap as the explicit `String(255)`
        constraint here, mirroring x_[scope]_case.subject for symmetry
        and matching the platform's sensible default for short-summary
        columns.

    Constraints honored (AAP Sections 0.7.1, 0.7.2, 0.7.4):
      - Scope-namespace exclusivity: `<name>` resolves to
        `x_[scope]_case_task` within the scoped application, and
        `<sys_scope>` / `<sys_package>` bind THIS dictionary record to
        the same scope by `source` attribute lookup. NO global-scope
        writes - the OOB tables `task`, `incident`, `sys_user`, etc.
        are never modified by this dictionary entry or any other artifact
        in the Update Set.
      - Zero hardcoded cross-reference sys_ids: the `<sys_scope>` and
        `<sys_package>` text-node values resolve by scope source name
        (`x_[scope]_case_management`), not by literal sys_id. The
        `<sys_id>` text-node value is THIS record's own deterministic
        primary key (MD5 of the canonical field identifier
        `x_[scope]_case_task.subject`) and is NOT a reference to any
        other record. The MD5 derivation guarantees that re-generation
        of this Update Set on any agent run produces a byte-identical
        `<sys_id>` (no random UUIDs), which is required for clean
        Update-Set re-import on a fresh PDI without creating duplicate
        sys_dictionary rows.
      - The literal `[scope]` placeholder is preserved per AAP convention;
        the PDI auto-assigns the actual scope id at App Engine Studio
        creation time. The placeholder appears in `<name>`, `<sys_scope>`,
        `<sys_package>`, and `<sys_update_name>` consistently.
      - mandatory=true at the dictionary level (AAP Section 0.5.7
        verbatim: "subject | String(255) | Mandatory"). This matches the
        source-side @Size(min=1) constraint on ArkCase's `title` field
        semantically (an empty string is rejected). A task without a
        subject would be impossible to identify in any list or related-
        list - the platform enforces this at every entry point: form
        submission, Table API insert, GlideRecord seed insert, and any
        future REST API call. AAP Section 0.7.1 ("Preserve the user-
        prompt's data-model field set verbatim. The exact field names,
        types, and constraints in the three tables MUST match the
        prompt - no additions, no renames, no type relaxations.") is
        honored exactly.
      - read_only=false: internal users with the case_manager role, and
        case_agent role on assigned cases (per AAP Section 0.5.6 ACL
        matrix), may correct an erroneous subject AFTER the task is
        created. Internal-user write authorization is governed by the
        table-level ACLs in ../acl/ - this dictionary entry deliberately
        does NOT carry per-role write_roles since the table-level ACLs
        apply uniformly across all editable fields on x_[scope]_case_task.
      - default_value is EMPTY (no implicit default) per AAP Section 0.5.7
        and the agent prompt's Phase 4 verbatim. Subject is the most
        important user-facing identifier of a task; defaulting silently
        to a placeholder string ("Untitled Task", "(no subject)", etc.)
        would silently mask submissions that failed mandatory enforcement
        and pollute the My Overdue Tasks report and the case form's task
        related list with semantically-empty rows.
      - audit=false per AAP Section 0.3.1 minimal-change clause and the
        agent prompt's Phase 4. Task subject is descriptive metadata, not
        a regulated lifecycle attribute (unlike case.status which carries
        audit=true because every state transition must be reconstructable
        post-hoc). The additional sys_audit row per update would be
        unnecessary overhead for a POC.
      - max_length=255 EXACTLY per AAP Section 0.5.7 verbatim. NOT 4000
        (description-style long-form free text is not present on
        x_[scope]_case_task at all - AAP Section 0.5.7's case_task table
        has no description column), NOT 100 (requester_name /
        requester_email-style identity strings are case-table-only),
        NOT 40 (number / type / status / priority controlled-vocabulary
        identifier strings). 255 is the standard ceiling on a free-form
        short-summary String column, consistent with x_[scope]_case.subject.
      - choice=0 = "Free-form String, no choice list" (NOT 3 like the
        type / status fields on the same case_task table). Subject is
        unconstrained natural-language text; constraining it to a choice
        list would defeat its purpose as a per-task unique human-readable
        label.
      - unique=false: multiple tasks with the same subject are explicitly
        permitted, both within a single case ("Send follow-up email"
        might appear three times on a complex case) and across cases
        ("Investigate and respond" is a common subject across many cases).
        Uniqueness across all tasks is intentionally NOT enforced; the
        auto-generated `number` field on the case_task table (per the
        accompanying ../numbers/sys_number_x_[scope]_case_task.xml record)
        is the unique identifier.
      - text_index=false per the agent prompt's Phase 6 verbatim. Tasks
        are a child entity always navigated through their parent case;
        users locate a task by opening its parent case and selecting it
        from the related list, not by performing free-form full-text
        search across the task table directly. A text index on a child
        table that is rarely queried by free-form search would carry
        storage and write-time costs without matching usage patterns.
        (Contrast with x_[scope]_case.subject, which has text_index=true
        because case-level free-form search is a primary user pattern.)
      - spell_check=false per the agent prompt's Phase 6 verbatim.
        Internal agents creating tasks frequently use short, abbreviation-
        heavy directives ("ETA req", "follow-up w/ legal", "verify ID");
        spell-check noise would degrade UX and surface false positives on
        domain abbreviations the platform has no dictionary for.
      - No reference target: this is a free-form String field, not a
        Reference field. All `<reference*>` elements are empty and
        `<table_reference>false</table_reference>`.
      - No PII: while the field stores synthetic task-summary phrases in
        the demo seed data, NO real names, real email addresses, real
        phone numbers, real organization names, or real task content from
        the source ArkCase database are placed in this column at any
        point in the build (per AAP Section 0.3.2 synthetic-data-only
        constraint). Demo seed values are fabricated phrases such as
        "Investigate inquiry details" or "Follow up with requester for
        additional information".

    Cross-references (AAP Section 0.5.2 dependency ordering):
      - This record MUST load AFTER:
          * ../tables/x_[scope]_case_task.xml (parent table; the
            `<name>x_[scope]_case_task</name>` element below references
            the table by name, and the table must exist before any of
            its dictionary entries can be attached)
          * ../app/sys_app/x_[scope]_case_management.xml and
            ../app/sys_scope/x_[scope].xml (scoped application records;
            <sys_scope> and <sys_package> resolve against them by source
            name)
      - This record MUST load BEFORE:
          * ../seed-data/tasks/x_[scope]_case_task_demo_*.xml (synthetic
            demo tasks per AAP Section 0.7.4 must populate this mandatory
            field with realistic non-PII summary phrases. The seed data
            references this column by `element=subject` and would fail to
            insert if this sys_dictionary record were absent)
          * ../reports/x_[scope]_my_overdue_tasks.xml (the list report
            includes `subject` as a visible column for at-a-glance
            recognition of each overdue task)
          * ../scripts/seed_demo_data.js (the idempotent server-side seed
            script writes synthetic subjects via
            GlideRecord.setValue('subject', ...))
          * ../flows/sub_flows/validate_resolved_transition.xml (when the
            "all tasks must be closed" gate iterates open tasks for an
            error-message hint, the iteration may surface the offending
            task's subject in the blocking-error context. The subflow
            does NOT depend on this dictionary entry for its primary
            blocking logic - the gate keys off `status != Closed` only -
            but reading `current.subject` for diagnostic display requires
            this column to exist)

    Source for the deterministic sys_id derivation:
        echo -n "x_[scope]_case_task.subject" | md5sum
        => 8cd658b766c404ce4445d191adabd14c

    The MD5 input is the canonical field identifier <name>.<element>,
    matching the same derivation pattern used across all other
    sys_dictionary records in this Update Set (verifiable by re-running
    md5sum on x_[scope]_case.subject => 96a737c3997894e2ba2aacb07aa4854e
    which matches ./x_[scope]_case_subject.xml's <sys_id>, and on
    x_[scope]_case_task.case => 25cae07ed16e95fd89a4c8013152ecc2 which
    matches ./x_[scope]_case_task_case.xml's <sys_id>).
-->
<record_update table="sys_dictionary">
    <sys_dictionary action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE">
        <active>true</active>
        <array>false</array>
        <attributes/>
        <audit>false</audit>
        <calculation/>
        <choice>0</choice>
        <choice_field/>
        <choice_table/>
        <column_label>Subject</column_label>
        <comments>Mandatory String(255) capturing the short summary or title of the task. Primary human-readable identifier in the case_task list view, the parent case's task related list, and the My Overdue Tasks report. Replaces ArkCase AcmTask.title (@Size(min=1)).</comments>
        <create_roles/>
        <default_value/>
        <defaultsort/>
        <delete_roles/>
        <dependent/>
        <dependent_on_field/>
        <display>true</display>
        <dynamic_creation>false</dynamic_creation>
        <dynamic_creation_script/>
        <dynamic_default_value/>
        <dynamic_ref_qual/>
        <element>subject</element>
        <element_reference>false</element_reference>
        <foreign_database/>
        <function_definition/>
        <function_field>false</function_field>
        <internal_type>string</internal_type>
        <mandatory>true</mandatory>
        <max_length>255</max_length>
        <name>x_[scope]_case_task</name>
        <next_element/>
        <primary>false</primary>
        <read_only>false</read_only>
        <read_roles/>
        <reference/>
        <reference_cascade_rule/>
